OL,3,CMuslims and non-Muslims invited to
OL,4,Ccreate 'one-of-a kind' Quran manuscript
OL,6,FVisitors will also have the
OL,7,Fopportunity to transcribe Quran verses
OL,8,Fonto traditional multicoloured hand-
OL,9,Ffinished calligraphy paper from
OL,10,FPakistan, to form the new Birmingham
OL,11,FQuran manuscript.
OL,13,FSome of the inks and pigments used
OL,14,Fwill be sourced from the Winterbourne
OL,15,FHouse & Gardens and the Birmingham
OL,16,FBotanical Gardens.
OL,18,FAfter transcription the book will be
OL,19,Fhand-bound and stitched using
OL,20,Ftraditional techniques and local
OL,21,Fmaterials.
